  <Subject Subject_ID="300053653">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300053652</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>needleworking (process) [300053652], needleworking and needleworking techniques [300239671], textile working processes and techniques [300239670], textile processes and techniques [300239669], processes and techniques by material [300053900], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the process in which a needle and thread or fine wire are used to stitch decorative designs into cloth, leather, paper, or other material. It may also refer to the process used to create machine-made imitations of hand-made embroidery.  For the weft patterning technique of weaving raised patterns on a woven textile, use "brocading."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045882/Dillmont, Complete Encyclopedia of Needlework (1996)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refiérase al proceso en el cual una aguja y un hilo torcido o un alambre fino se utilizan para coser diseños decorativos en un paño, cuero, papel, u otro material. Puede también referirse al proceso usado para crear imitaciones hechas a máquina del bordado realizado a mano. Para la técnica que modela la trama del tejido y sus patrones de sobrerelieve en un textil tejido, utilizar "brocado.”</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar het procedé waarbij een naald en een draad of een dunne metaaldraad worden gebruikt voor het stikken van decoratieve patronen in stof, leer, papier of ander materiaal. Gebruik 'brocheren' voor de techniek van het aanbrengen van inslagpatronen, waarmee verhoogde patronen worden ingeweven in een geweven stof.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>利用針與繩線或細線在布品、皮革、紙張或其他材料上縫繡裝飾圖案的過程，亦可指稱利用機器製作類似手工刺繡花樣的過程。若是用於指稱將圖案浮織於布品上的緯錦織法，則稱為「錦緞織法」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
